table_caption: Participant demographic and clinical information. A Wilcoxon rank-sum test was used to find differences in SF-36-subscores between HC and LBP. Higher scores indicate healthier functioning. PF = physical functioning, RLP = role limitations due to physical health problems, P = bodily pain, GH = general health, EF = energy and fatigue, SF = social functioning, RLE = role limitations due to emotional problems, EW = emotional well-being. (* = p < 0.05, ** = p < 0.01, *** = p < 0.001; p values have been corrected for multiple comparisons using FDR).
